%F A000316 a(n) = A000459(n)*2^n.
%F A000316 G.f.: Sum_{j=0..n*k} coeff(R(x, n, k), x, j)*(-1)^j*(n*k-j)! where n is the number of kinds of cards, k is the number of cards of each kind (2 in this case) and R(x, n, k) is the rook polynomial given by R(x, n, k)=(k!^2*Sum_{j=0..k} x^j/((k-j)!^2*j!))^n (see Riordan). coeff(R(x, n, k), x, j) indicates the coefficient for x^j of the rook polynomial.
%F A000316 From _Dan Dima_, Dec 17 2006: (Start)
%F A000316 a(n) = n! * Sum_{a,b >= 0, a+b <= n} (-1)^b * 2^(a+2*b) * (2*n-2*a-b)! / (a! * b! * (n-a-b)!).
%F A000316 a(n) = n * a(n-1) + n! * 4^n * Sum_{a=0..n} (-1)^a / (a! * 2^a). (End)
%F A000316 a(n) = 2^n * round(2^(n/2 + 3/4)*Pi^(-1/2)*exp(-2)*n!*BesselK(1/2+n,2^(1/2))) for n > 0. - _Mark van Hoeij_, Oct 30 2011
%F A000316 Recurrence: (2*n-3)*a(n) = 2*(n-1)*(2*n-1)^2*a(n-1) + 4*(n-1)*(2*n-3)*a(n-2) - 16*(n-2)*(n-1)*(2*n-1)*a(n-3). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 07 2013
%F A000316 From _Peter Bala_, Jul 07 2014: (Start)
%F A000316 a(n) = Integral_{x>=0} exp(-x)*(x^2 - 4*x + 2)^n dx. Cf. A000166(n) = Integral_{x>=0} exp(-x)*(x - 1)^n dx.
%F A000316 Asymptotic: a(n) ~ (2*n)!*exp(-2)*( 1 - 1/(2*n) - 23/(96*n^2) + O(1/n^3) ). See Nicolaescu. (End)
%e A000316 There are 80 ways of achieving zero matches when there are 2 cards of each kind and 3 kinds of card so a(3)=80.
%e A000316 Among the 24 (multiset) permutations of {1,1',2,2'}, only {2,2',1,1'}, {2',2,1,1'}, {2,2',1',1} and {2',2,1',1} have no fixed points, thus a(2)=4.
%p A000316 p := (x,k)->k!^2*sum(x^j/((k-j)!^2*j!),j=0..k); R := (x,n,k)->p(x,k)^n; f := (t,n,k)->sum(coeff(R(x,n,k),x,j)*(t-1)^j*(n*k-j)!,j=0..n*k); seq(f(0,n,2), n=0..18);
